passages.text: F2Q26 Review: Beat an Raise Sep Out Course for Acceleration of Growth FY26 and Beyond; Raise PT

Pure Storage pleasantly surprised investors with significant revenue momentum in the quarter, helped by broad- based strength across the portfolio, as well as an improvement in visibility for the remainder of the fiscal year, particularly with the company expressing greater confidence in relation to customer spending intent as the underlying macro remains more resilient than feared earlier in the year. The confidence in relation to customer spending intent is reflected in the company opting to raise the full- year revenue guide by \(\sim \$ 100\) mn relative to the prior guide, following an \(11 \mathrm{mn}\) beat in F2Q relative to guidance. While the momentum in revenue performance and the outlook do stand out relative to peers with more modest upsides and consistent outlooks, it is important to highlight that peer companies are being challenged by pullbacks in relation to Public Sector spending, which Pure Storage has limited exposure to. Looking beyond the momentum with Enterprise customers, Pure Storage continued to make progress on its engagement with Meta, including the customer initiating first volume deployments resulting in first revenues from this engagement in F2Q. Engagement with other hyperscaler customers is also progressing with Pure Storage looking to enable customers to replace raw storage with DFMs, although timing of potential conversion of engagements to wins remains uncertain. The revenue contribution from hyperscaler engagements will be minimal in FY26, but will be a key component of our (and investor) expectations for acceleration of growth for the company beyond FY26, following an already guided acceleration in the updated outlook in relation to \(14\%\) revenue growth in FY26 vs. \(12\%\) in FY25. Beyond the revenue drivers, the company raised confidence in the margin outlook with gross margin in the quarter tracking ahead of expectations in F2Q and the company outlined expectations for gross margins to continue to improve with an increase in subscription mix within aggregate revenues, although offset by the company opting to preserve flexibility in relation to investments to support growth and progress on new platforms, but in aggregate still able to support our above- consensus earnings forecasts. We are raising our Dec- 26 price target to \(80\) from \(70\) to reflect the more robust outlook and higher confidence in relation to growth acceleration.

F2Q26 (JuI- end) Results: Strong revenue and operating margins combined with favorable tax rate drive EPS beat. Revenue tracked to \(\) 861\(mn vs. JPM\) \mathrm{e} \(of\) \ \(845\) mn and consensus of \(\) 846\(mn, driven by robust broad- based demand across all segments. Meanwhile, gross margins tracked to\) 74.1\% \(vs. JPM\) \mathrm{e} \(of\) 70.9\% \(and consensus of\) 70.7\% \(, driven by a favorable mix shift between product and software revenue, customers opting for higher- end solutions, and pricing discipline. Operating margins tracked to\) 15.1\% \(relative to JPM\) \mathrm{e} \(of\) 15.0\% \(, consensus of\) 14.8\% \(, and implied guide of\) 14.8\% \(, which in combination with a favorable tax rate drove EPS ahead of expectations at\) \ \(0.43\) vs. JPM \(of\) \ \(0.37\) and consensus of \(\) 0.39\$
F3Q26 (Oct- end) Guidance: Better- than- anticipated revenue and operating margins on strong demand expectations. Pure Storage is guiding

Pure Storage is a leading provider of software- defined all- flash data storage solutions for the enterprise. It is one of the very few companies that is able to improve the reliability factor of cheap consumer- grade flash with the help of software, thus driving cost efficiencies to make flash broadly palatable for the enterprise. Additionally, its maintenance program offering very compelling lifetime value for customers, along with other patent- protected innovations such as non- disruptive upgrades, superior data- reduction capability, and a highly automated easy- to- use interface, shapes its competitive advantage and positions it very favorably in the market. While the competitive landscape for solid- state arrays continues to evolve quickly as the legacy storage vendors recognize the threat that flash poses to their core business and are quickly pivoting toward it, we think Pure's \(100\%\) focus on flash- based storage, its rapid innovation cycle enabling it to bring new technologies (like NVMe) first to the market, along with its very high customer satisfaction, are helping Pure stay ahead of the curve. We expect Pure to continue to grow bookings at a fairly good clip while generating sustainable positive OCF and P&L profitability.

We are increasing our December 2026 price target to \(80 (vs. 570 prior) based on valuing our 2027 EPS estimates on a target P/E multiple of \(29x,\) which is roughly in line with the current trading multiple and higher relative to storage peers like NetApp, given a better revenue growth profile driven by the \(100\%\) focus on flash- based storage.

Pure Storage is a leading provider of software- defined all- flash data storage solutions for the enterprise. It is one of the very few companies that is able to improve the reliability factor of cheap consumer- grade flash with the help of software, thus driving cost- efficiencies to make flash broadly palatable for the enterprise. Additionally, its maintenance program offering very compelling lifetime value for customers, along with other patent- protected innovations such as non- disruptive upgrades, superior data- reduction capability, and a highly automated easy- to- use interface, shapes its competitive advantage and positions it very favorably in the market. While the competitive landscape for solid- state arrays continues to evolve quickly as the legacy storage vendors recognize the threat that flash poses to their core business and are quickly pivoting toward it, we think Pure's \(100\%\) focus on flash- based storage, its rapid innovation cycle enabling it to bring new technologies (like NVMe) first to the market, along with its very high customer satisfaction, are helping Pure stay ahead of the curve. We expect Pure to continue to grow revenue and billings at a fairly good clip while generating sustainable positive OCF and P&L profitability.

We are increasing our December 2026 price target to \(\) 80\((vs.\) \ \(70\) prior) based on valuing our 2027 EPS estimates on a target P/E multiple of \(29x\) which is roughly in line with the current trading multiple and higher relative to storage peers like NetApp, given a better revenue growth profile driven by the \(100\%\) focus on flash- based storage.
